About this item

  • 24 Hours Health Tracking: The smart watch for kids uses high-performance optical sensors to act as a fitness tracker in a timely and accurate manner, recording your child's daily walking steps, distance and calories. Sync the child's fitness watch with your phone via Bluetooth and access detailed data on the JYouPro app. the fitness watch through shown detailed data to help kids build up a good lifestyle.
  • Real-time Heart Rate and Sleep Tracking: Kids Fitness Tracker can automatically monitors your child's heart rate in real-time and tracks their sleep quality at night, including deep sleep, light sleep, and awake states. You can also create a sleep plan for your kids, set vibrating alarm clock can wake up your child without disturbing others and help your child develop good sleeping habits.
  • Friendly for Children and Easy to Charge: The fitness watch is made of flexible and durable TPU material without any harmful substances.Light weight, easy to install, hard and strong, kids can enjoy sports, hiking, games and more. And with a comfortable and adjustable strap making it suitable for kids of all ages. Quick and easy charging with built-in USB, charge for 2 hours and the fitness tracker battery will last up to 7 days.
  • Multi functional Kids Watch: Kids fitness smart watch with pedometer, stopwatch, alarm clock, time display, calorie count, music control, remote camera recording, etc. 4 sports modes include walking, running, cycling, hiking. The watch for kids support multiple smart alerts, including incoming calls, SMS, SNS messages (Facebook, WhatsApp, etc.) With an IP67 waterproof rating, your children can safely wear this watch when sweating, washing hands and rains.
  • Gifts for Boys Girls and Teens: Waterproof smart watch for kids with stylish and cute design. The 0.96-inch color screen has adjustable brightness and the display lights up automatically when you lift your wrist. Kids can also choose from 4 different themed finishes. and is compatible with most android and iOS phones (android 8.0+ and iOS 12.0+). fitness watch has many interesting and useful functions, it will be a great gift for boys, girls, teenagers. Intended for ages 3+ years.

Product Description

Fashion Fitness Tracker Watch for Boys Girls

Main Functions of this Kids Fitness Tracker

  • Activity Tracker (steps, distance, calories)
  • 3 Wallpaper to choose
  • 4 Sport Modes (Runing, Walking, Biking, Hiking)
  • 24-hour Heart Rate / Sleep Monitor
  • Stopwatch / Timer / Alarm Clock
  • Message Notifications / Calls Reminder
  • Find Phone / Remote Camera Control
  • Brightness Adjustment
  • IP67 Waterproof

Silicone Rubber Watch Strap Designed For Kids, Adjustable Fitness Tracker Strap, More Suitable for Growing Kids

Heart Rate Monitor Tracker

The kids fitness smartwatch will automatically monitor your child's real-time daily heart rate throughout the day. Also, you can track your kids heart rate with the app.

Sleep Tracker

The fitness tracker for children will automatically analyze the sleep quality of the child and show you the sleep data of deep sleep and light sleep. You can view sleep data on the watch and in the app

Message and Call Reminder

Kids fitness tracker watch supports phone calls reminding (can't answer phone and can't use sim card), SMS and SNS notifications (Facebook, WhatsApp, LinkedIn, Instagram, and Twitter, etc)., avoiding missing important messages or call

Multiple Watch Face

There are 3 watch faces, which your children can freely switch between and express their style.

Multiple Sport Modes

The kids sport watch supports multiple sports modes: walking, running, cycling, hiking. Allows you to track various data in real time during exercise. and records activity all day, calculates steps, moving distance, calories burned, as well as active minutes.

Timer and Stopwatch

The stopwatch function is very useful for sports. The fitness tracker can be used as a timer when your child wants to set fitness goals or needs time to remind himself of his routine.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

4 out of 5 stars
Fun starter watch for fitness and sleep tracking for kids
The watch is for my 9yo son, and i gave it to him on xmas. He was really excited. The watchband was way too long and it only fit on his wrist on the second to absolute tightest hole selection! See photo!One issue I have is the default mode is metric. In America, we don't often use the metric system to measure height and weight. There is no option to change this.The watch also starts in 24 hr mode, but at least it csn be changed to 12 hr format.The steps are fun, bc I have a Fitbit watch and now he csn try to keep up with my steps! He asks to compare across the day. I like that it keeps him active. It also csn send reminders if he is sitting and watching TV or on his tablet longer than I like.One thing I was really interested in was the sleep tracker. My watch shows REM, light, and deep sleep cycles as well as time awake, giving me a score. I expected something similar. However, I was very disappointed in how simplistic the sleep tracking is. It only shows deep and light sleep (and awake time). So far the numbers are even (3 hrs deep, 7 hrs light, 10 hrs total -- no minutes, so I am not sure if it is rounding?)He had been really excited when I told him it would be able to tell him when he had dreams (REM) like my watch. But it doesn't mention it at all, so it was a disappointment for him, too.It also is great the watch lasts a week between charges, and unlike my Fitbit, it doesn't need a weird charge plug adapter!If the settings could allow it to Imperial measurements and not metric, it would be much better. I had to use Google to calculate weight and height into metric for his profile.Also, forget about it tracking activities. It doesn't have GPS, so the activity distances are determined by the phone being kept on him (which is actually my phone since he is too young for a phone).Simple, cheap tracker for kids - not bad, but could use a lot of improvement!

  • Andrea S. / DJ Purity
    4.0 out of 5 stars Fun starter watch for fitness and sleep tracking for kids
    Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2024
    Color: BlueVerified Purchase
    The watch is for my 9yo son, and i gave it to him on xmas. He was really excited. The watchband was way too long and it only fit on his wrist on the second to absolute tightest hole selection! See photo!

    One issue I have is the default mode is metric. In America, we don't often use the metric system to measure height and weight. There is no option to change this.

    The watch also starts in 24 hr mode, but at least it csn be changed to 12 hr format.

    The steps are fun, bc I have a Fitbit watch and now he csn try to keep up with my steps! He asks to compare across the day. I like that it keeps him active. It also csn send reminders if he is sitting and watching TV or on his tablet longer than I like.

    One thing I was really interested in was the sleep tracker. My watch shows REM, light, and deep sleep cycles as well as time awake, giving me a score. I expected something similar. However, I was very disappointed in how simplistic the sleep tracking is. It only shows deep and light sleep (and awake time). So far the numbers are even (3 hrs deep, 7 hrs light, 10 hrs total -- no minutes, so I am not sure if it is rounding?)

    He had been really excited when I told him it would be able to tell him when he had dreams (REM) like my watch. But it doesn't mention it at all, so it was a disappointment for him, too.

    It also is great the watch lasts a week between charges, and unlike my Fitbit, it doesn't need a weird charge plug adapter!

    If the settings could allow it to Imperial measurements and not metric, it would be much better. I had to use Google to calculate weight and height into metric for his profile.

    Also, forget about it tracking activities. It doesn't have GPS, so the activity distances are determined by the phone being kept on him (which is actually my phone since he is too young for a phone).

    Simple, cheap tracker for kids - not bad, but could use a lot of improvement!
